<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1414,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,595,1594,1620]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Description of Japanese material.</emphasis>
A live (incomplete) individual 
<quantity box="[939,1017,1594,1620]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1124,1222,1594,1620]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
wide in preclitellar segments, segments 42+. Body light red when living. Prostomium conical (
<figureCitation box="[995,1081,1630,1656]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-154@5.[151,1436,417,1202]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook from Sapporo, Japan. A, dorsal chaeta in III; B and C variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; D, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; E, the same in a posterior segment; F, sagittal section of anterior segments; G, parasagittal section of genital segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). No distinct secondary annulations. Pharynx in II–III, covered with a thin layer of pharyngeal glands. Chloragogen cells from VI on, thinly covering gut. No stomachal dilatation. Transverse blood vessels forming loops in II–VII, thick in VIII and IX. Individuals living in soft mud tube with adherent foreign matter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1414,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Chaetae all crotchets, with form, size and number not different between dorsal and ventral bundles. Those in anterior segments (II–V or II–VI, 
<figureCitation box="[539,660,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-154@5.[151,1436,417,1202]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook from Sapporo, Japan. A, dorsal chaeta in III; B and C variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; D, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; E, the same in a posterior segment; F, sagittal section of anterior segments; G, parasagittal section of genital segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3A–C</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than the following ones, 7–9 per bundle, 
<quantity box="[1320,1436,1810,1836]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" metricValueMax="9.4" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="87.0" valueMax="94.0" valueMin="80.0">80–94 µm</quantity>
long, with distal nodulus and with rudimentary upper tooth or simple pointed distal end; those from VI or VII on (
<figureCitation box="[160,271,1882,1908]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-154@5.[151,1436,417,1202]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook from Sapporo, Japan. A, dorsal chaeta in III; B and C variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; D, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; E, the same in a posterior segment; F, sagittal section of anterior segments; G, parasagittal section of genital segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3D,E</figureCitation>
) 4–6 per bundle, 
<quantity box="[469,585,1882,1908]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="62.0" valueMin="48.0">48–62 µm</quantity>
long. Nodulus at 1/3 from distal end, and distal end brush-like with a series of teeth gradually decreasing in size from lower to upper (
<figureCitation box="[801,918,1918,1944]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,788,812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,765]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,166,765]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook, from Sapporo, Japan.SEM photomicrographs of dorsal chaetal bundle (A) and two chaetae (B) in a mid- segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671504" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671504/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 4A,B</figureCitation>
). No lateral expansions in the chaetal shafts in any segments. No modified genital chaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1414,2016]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Clitellum surround the segments from beginning of X to end of XII, with the wall 
<quantity box="[1153,1270,1990,2016]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="16.0">16–30 µm</quantity>
thick. Gonads and copulatory organs paired (
<figureCitation box="[501,594,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-154@5.[151,1436,417,1202]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook from Sapporo, Japan. A, dorsal chaeta in III; B and C variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; D, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; E, the same in a posterior segment; F, sagittal section of anterior segments; G, parasagittal section of genital segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Testes and ovaries attached respectively to posterior sides of septa 9/10 and 10/11. Male funnels large. Vasa deferentia short and not winding, 
<quantity box="[943,1030,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="240.0">240 µm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1143,1217,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 µm</quantity>
wide, connected to apical end of atrium. Atria bean-shaped, 
<quantity box="[606,693,222,249]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="150.0">150 µm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[804,877,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 µm</quantity>
in maximum diameter. Prostate glands as large as atria. Ejaculatory ducts not detected. Penes 
<quantity box="[638,710,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="90.0">90 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[781,853,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 µm</quantity>
wide, two-layered with ordinary cuticular covering, and separate openings lateral to ventral chaetal line at middle of XI. Spermathecae in X, small (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1313,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-154@5.[151,1436,417,1202]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aulodrilus americanus Brinkhurst &amp; Cook from Sapporo, Japan. A, dorsal chaeta in III; B and C variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; D, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; E, the same in a posterior segment; F, sagittal section of anterior segments; G, parasagittal section of genital segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); ampullae ovoid in shape, 
<quantity box="[325,396,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 µm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[503,575,330,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 µm</quantity>
wide; ducts stout and well-marked off from the ampullae, about 
<quantity box="[1288,1374,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="100.0">100 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[151,266,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25 µm</quantity>
wide, opening laterally at middle of X. Sperm sac in X. Egg sac observed to extend as far back as XII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4671500" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4671500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4671500/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" startId="5.[151,250,1225,1249]" targetBox="[157,1430,425,1197]" targetPageId="5">
