Brinkhurst &amp; Cook
</taxonomicName>
from Sapporo, Japan. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[938,956,1225,1249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A</emphasis>
, dorsal chaeta in III; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1170,1187,1225,1249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">B</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1235,1253,1225,1249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C</emphasis>
variation of distal ends of dorsal chaetae in anterior segments; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[605,623,1261,1285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">D</emphasis>
, dorsal chaeta in a mid-segment; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[967,984,1261,1285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E</emphasis>
, the same in a posterior segment; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1334,1349,1261,1285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F</emphasis>
